<body>
    <h1>02 - Install Python Dependencies And Configure Robot Framework Lang=
uage Server</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <div style=3D"display: none;">
<br>
</div>
<p>Every Robot Framework Project should have at minimum a requirements.txt =
for pip installation, but ideally also have <span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0=
);"><a href=3D"/display/RFR/Pipenv">Pipenv</a></span>.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Hopefully Python is already installed, but if not the recommended versio=
n of Python is 3.8.x</p>
<h4 id=3D"id-02InstallPythonDependenciesAndConfigureRobotFrameworkLanguageS=
erver-PipenvInstallationofLocalEnvironment(PreferredMethod)"><br>Pipenv Ins=
tallation of Local Environment (Preferred Method)</h4>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">from&nbsp;cmd install&nbsp;pipenv=
:</span></li>
</ul>
<pre>python&nbsp;-m&nbsp;pip&nbsp;install&nbsp;pipenv</pre>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">if&nbsp;needed:&nbsp;update&nbsp;=
pip (there will be text output indicating it needs updating)</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">From&nbsp;the&nbsp;root&nbsp;dire=
ctory&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;Robot&nbsp;Framework&nbsp;project&nbsp;(the&nbs=
p;one&nbsp;containing&nbsp;a&nbsp;Pipfile&nbsp;file)&nbsp;Execute&nbsp;this=
&nbsp;command&nbsp;to&nbsp;install&nbsp;the&nbsp;python&nbsp;required&nbsp;=
packages:</span></li>
</ul>
<pre>pipenv&nbsp;install --python 3.8 --dev</pre>
<h4 id=3D"id-02InstallPythonDependenciesAndConfigureRobotFrameworkLanguageS=
erver-PipInstallMethod(usefulforfullenvironmentinstalls)NOTFORLOCALSYSTEMSL=
IKEYOURLAPTOP"><br>Pip Install Method (useful for full environment installs=
) NOT FOR LOCAL SYSTEMS LIKE YOUR LAPTOP</h4>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">From&nbsp;the&nbsp;root&nbsp;dire=
ctory&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;Robot&nbsp;Framework&nbsp;project&nbsp;(the&nbs=
p;one&nbsp;containing&nbsp;a&nbsp;requirements.txt file)&nbsp;Execute&nbsp;=
this&nbsp;command&nbsp;to&nbsp;install&nbsp;the&nbsp;python&nbsp;required&n=
bsp;packages:</span></li>
</ul>
<pre>pip install requirements.txt</pre>
<h4 id=3D"id-02InstallPythonDependenciesAndConfigureRobotFrameworkLanguageS=
erver-SetthePythonInterpreterForVSCode:">Set the Python Interpreter For VSC=
ode:</h4>
<p>Review this article:&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/=
python/python-tutorial" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://co=
de.visualstudio.com/docs/python/python-tutorial</a></p>
<p>In the case of pipenv the interpreter path will point to the virtualenv =
that was created when you executed 'pipenv install'</p>
<h1 id=3D"id-02InstallPythonDependenciesAndConfigureRobotFrameworkLanguageS=
erver-ConfigureRobotFrameworkLanguageServer"><br>Configure Robot Framework =
Language Server</h1>
<p>Once python is installed and possibly(hopefully) pipenv is installed the=
 workplace configuration file will need to be updated.</p>
<p>First, review the steps found here:&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://code.visuals=
tudio.com/docs/editor/workspaces" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">=
https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/editor/workspaces</a></p>
<p>Once there is a settings.json file created in a .vscode directory update=
 it with these settings:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>settings.json</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{
    "editor.rulers" : [120],
    "editor.codeActionsOnSave": {"source.fixAll": true, "source.organizeImp=
orts": true},
    "files.trimTrailingWhitespace": true,
    "python.envFile": "${workspaceFolder}/.env",
    "python.linting.pylintEnabled": true,
    "python.linting.flake8Enabled": true,
    "python.analysis.extraPaths": [
        "${workspaceFolder}/CustomLibraries",
        "${workspaceFolder}/Resources"
    ],
    "[python]": {
        "editor.tabSize": 4,
        "editor.insertSpaces": true,
        "editor.detectIndentation": false
    },
    "robot.language-server.python": "&lt;Location of python executable that=
 has Robot Framework Installed",
    "robot.lint.robocop.enabled": true,
    "robot.pythonpath": [
        "${workspaceFolder}"
    ]
}</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<h4 id=3D"id-02InstallPythonDependenciesAndConfigureRobotFrameworkLanguageS=
erver-Noteaboutthe&quot;robot.language-server.python&quot;setting:">Note ab=
out the&nbsp;"robot.language-server.python" setting:</h4>
<p>This need to be the absolute path to where pip or pipenv has installed t=
he dependencies. In the case of pipenv it is the name of the vitrualenv set=
 up when you ran 'pipenv install'.</p>
<p>WARNING</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-war=
ning">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-error confluence-inform=
ation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>If you ever need to run the 'pipenv --rm' command&nbsp; or run 'pipenv i=
nstall' do these things:</p>
<ol>
<li>In your workplace settings.json comment out the<span style=3D"color: rg=
b(0,51,102);">&nbsp;robot.language-server.python line</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">Reload the VSCode window (it shou=
ld prompt after you comment out the line.</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">Then run the pipenv command.</spa=
n></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">Afterwards you can uncomment the =
line and you may need to update the setting.</span></li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
